                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "B P65, P38 MAPK, P-P38, c-JUN, and Caspase-1 proteins in liver tissues were higher in the NAFLD model group compared to the control group. Treatment with groups 1 and 2 resulted in significantly decreased levels of TC, TG, ALT, AST, LDL-C, LPS, MDA, as well as reduced liver TC, TG, and free fatty acid (FFA) content compared to the model group. Conversely, SOD and HDL-C levels were significantly increased in the treatment groups. The levels of ALT, AST, LPS, and MDA in Treatment Group 2 were significantly lower than those in Treatment Group 1, while SOD and HDL-C levels were significantly increased. Liver TLR-4, MyD88, NF-kBP65, P38 MAPK, P-P38, and Caspase 1 protein expression in Treatment Groups 1 and 2 were significantly lower than in the model group, with Treatment Group 2 showing lower levels compared to Treatment Group 1. Conclusion: The concurrent administration of Daning tablets and Bifidobacterium has been shown to effectively ameliorate hepatic function impairment in NAFLD rats by attenuating oxidative stress, reducing inflammatory cytokine levels, and potentially inhibiting TR4/NF-kBP65/My D88 activation, thereby exerting protective effects on the liver in NAFLD."
